==Chinese==

===Etymology===
From Simplified Chinese: [[辽宁]]; Traditional Chinese: [[遼寧]]; pinyin: Liáoníng; "Liao" is an ancient name for this region, which was adopted by the Liao Dynasty (Khitan Empire) which ruled this area between 907 and 1125. "Níng" means "peacefulness."

===Proper noun===
'''Liaoning'''

# A coastal province in northeastern China.

